  "texts": [
    "We will discuss the implications of this in Section 7.1.1 in the discussion.",
    "This paper contributes new insights into how the LLM-as-a-Judge evaluation approach compares to evaluations conducted by SMEs for domain-specific tasks.",
    "Our research highlights the limitations of relying solely on LLMs for evaluation, and the importance of keeping the human, specifically the SME, in the loop for tasks that require expert knowledge.",
    "In this section, we explore the potential reasons behind the observed patterns in our findings.",
    "We then discuss key design implications that developers and designers should consider when designing and choosing the method for evaluating the quality of LLM outputs for domain-specific tasks."
  ]
